# When the UI runs inside the Webflow Designer extension iframe, requests cannot use relative /api paths.
# Set this to your deployed IconDock API origin (no trailing slash), e.g.:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-api.example.com
#
# Local dev defaults (if unset):
# - Vite (localhost:5173): `/api` is proxied to the backend — no env needed.
# - `webflow extension serve` (localhost:1337) and hosted Designer (`*.webflow-ext.com`): API calls go to
#   http://localhost:8787 — start the backend (`cd backend && npm run dev`).
# If the browser blocks http://localhost from an https://*.webflow-ext.com iframe, set VITE_API_BASE_URL to
# http://127.0.0.1:8787 or use an HTTPS tunnel to your API, then rebuild (`npm run build`).
